HEADWORD: Fabianism
<hw>Fabianism</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>the principles and beliefs of or
similar to those of the Fabian Society, advocating socialism to be
established by gradual reforms within the law.</def>
<mark>[British]</mark>⟦br⟧
